also one of the youngest (ho is but a
few years out of college) Yet upon
election to the Georgia State Legislature he was characteristic y a sub«
ject of controversy when i really denied a seat by fellow legislature —
apparently due to his conservation of
the U.S. position in Vietnam,
Affect Senators, compression
Mr. Bond has since been stated and
today continues to be heard on basic
issues of freedom: the freedom of the
people of South Vietnam for selfrdeterminafion, that of metro in America and
the freedom of Choice in military service to one‘s country. '
Bond’s voice now resource far outside the narrow combines of Georgia
politics. Last Saturday, after a conference at bikini, The Bahamas, on a
new black political organization, Bond
spoke in Des points, at a conference
studying the question of compulsory
military construction.
At the Des points meeting (held at
American Friends Service Committee
headquarters) this reporter asked Mr.
Bond about the upcoming “Mass Spring
civilization" at which he will make keyword address.
Asked about the efficacy of another
demonstration, Bond said, “Some people
downloads the effect of concentrations,
but, although I don’t think we can reach
